The HSP TH1RTE3N Glock Handgun sights were designed based on the science of how the human eye acquires sight alignment and sight picture under precision or stress sight picture situations.  Handgun sights are installed on a handgun to add more precision; this is what the HSP13 were designed around.  Under “critical stress” shooting, we know that the Body Alarm Response (BAR) instantly takes control and increases the blood flow to the center field of vision.  This in return increases your visual efficiency on the threat.  During this immediate process, it is very difficult to focus on anything other than the threat.  Your eyes observe, your brain orients, and you then decide on an action to take.  During this immediate BAR response process, you will look through your sights with your focal plane fixed on the target due to it being a positive and natural human defense mechanism.  With this theory in mind, the widths of the front sight or rear sight notch are irrelevant.  The idea that your front sight and or rear notch need to be large for faster target acquisition is misguided, according to current research by visual experts.   However, precision sight picture does matter when the information continues to the higher cognitive portion of the brain during situations where a decision has consciously been made to use a higher level of precision for hostage taker or long-range shots for example.  In this case, the HSP 13 sights are designed with a .125 front width sight and a .125 rear sight notch. This will refine the sight picture during the trigger press, decreasing human error and increasing hit probability on a precision target. -TH1RTE3N sights are precision CNC machined from heat treated1 416 stainless and finished in Black Oxide. -TH1RTE3N sights are hard duty / carry sights with a distinctive rear sight charging cuts for single hand applications. -TH1RTE3N front sight diameters are .160 height by .125 wide and come with a .070 tritium front sight insert. -TH1RTE3N rear sight diameters are .160 height with .125 bottom tapered notch, optional in black out or dual .070 Tritium inserts. -Please use a .050 Allen Head Tool for Rear Sight installation 100% made and manufactured in  the USA

title: For Sale:  FNH PS90 GEN 3
postcontent: Another rare firearm from my fathers collection, when he passed I had no idea the collection he left behind for his grandchildren. He was a retired military and law enforcement and he loved rare firearms what ever he could find he collected. This is a rare ps90 only a small amount were made this was the first production of the gen 3 they wanted it to look different and standout but they discontinued the entire receiver due to it was to expensive to make compared to the standard versions you see earlier and today as you can see in the pictue. it's all one piece with a low profile eye of sight for any optic, (optics included) it's ingenuity at its best. Has the gen3 trigger pack these are not the gen 4 triggers with after market parts to make a gen 3 as seen online this is the real deal all genuine fn parts. This makes this firearm rarer than rare very hard to find gen3, you won't find them in this configuration not your usual ps90. This looks to be new I am not sure still in factory plastic when retrieved from his war room as you can see in the photo no usage marks where they should be. this comes with a fifty round magazine.
